<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-363] Replace numerical compression codes in config with something human readable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-363</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently we have compression codes like 1 or 2, which is pretty unintuitive. What does 1 mean?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should replace these with human-readable codes like &quot;snappy&quot;, &quot;gzip&quot;, or &quot;none&quot; and change the documentation. We can continue to support the existing integer codes in addition for backwards compatibility with existing configurations.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
